{"body": "Thanks for the comments and remarks.\r\nI agree with @carlosantoniodasilva, that just yielding it back and setting attributes, is not an enough to validate this change.\r\n\r\nThe biggest advantage, in my opinion, comes from encapsulation and setting defaults:\r\n\r\n``` ruby\r\n  user.update_attributes(user_params) do |u|\r\n    u.username ||= 'temp_username'\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  def user_params\r\n   params.require(:user).permit(:username)\r\n  end\r\n```", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/21575389", "created_at": "2013-07-25T18:42:08Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11599#issuecomment-21575389", "updated_at": "2013-07-25T19:07:07Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 11599, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/versioncontrol/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/versioncontrol/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/versioncontrol/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/versioncontrol", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/versioncontrol/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/versioncontrol", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/versioncontrol/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/413ff2985979bee219caee4b4eadfbbf?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F8e207bffcc474cbb746cc72b44980006.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/versioncontrol/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/versioncontrol/received_events", "gravatar_id": "413ff2985979bee219caee4b4eadfbbf", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/versioncontrol/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "versioncontrol", "type": "User", "id": 527458, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/versioncontrol/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d2e3bd3543c151007ee0"}, "id": 21575389, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11599"}
